rstanding their rights as parents, and their children’s rights in school.</li>						<li id="n13">Parents reported a significant boost in self-confidence regarding their parenting skills, getting their children ready for school, and advocating on behalf of their children.</li>					</ul>										<p id="n14">						<a href="apdocs/apne.pdf" id="n15">click here for the full report</a>					</p>				</div> <!-- end textbox -->												<!-- LEFT PANE				====================================== -->															<div class="two-thirds column alpha" id="n16">								<!-- AP IN THE NEWS  -->										<div name="AP IN THE NEWS" class="add-bottom" id="n17">											<h5 class="ruled add-bottom google red-orange edit-txt" id="n18">AP in the News</h5>																					<div class="textBox edit" id="n19">							<ul class="">															<li id="n20"><a href="apdocs/wsj.pdf" class="" id="n21">WSJ: "Hispanics Get Help Giving Their Kids a Boost</a></li>								<li id="n22"><a href="apdocs/poder.pdf" id="n23">Poder: Bridging the Hispanic Achievement Gap</a></li>								<li id="n24"><a href="apdocs/ztt.pdf" id="n25">Zero to Three: Beyond a Haircut, Lunch&nbsp;Pale, and New&nbsp;Shoes</a></li>								<li id="n26"><a href="apdocs/EdSource.pdf" id="n27">Edsource: Parenting classes tailored for Latino families show promise in closing the achievment gap</a></li>								<li id="n28"><a href="apdocs/abqj.pdf" id="n29">ABQ Journal</a></li>								<li id="n30"><a href="apdocs/bspot.pdf" id="n31">Bright Spots</a></li>							</ul>							<ul class="a">								<li id="n32"><a href="http://www.hfrp.org/publications-resources/browse-our-publications/parents-as-agents-of-change?utm_source=Authors&utm_medium=email&utm_term=leading_gutierrez&utm_campaign=FINE2013Sept" id="n33">Harvard Family Research Project: Parents&nbsp;as Agents of Change</a></li>								<li id="n34"><a href="http://www.hfrp.org/publications-resources/browse-our-publications/padres-de-famili